<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFF13929EBD2C6E0FA925996" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF13929EBD2C6E0FEAA5ADB" blockId="95.[227,341,467,493]" box="[227,341,467,493]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<heading id="5A24A609FFF13929EBD2C6E0FEAA5ADB" bold="true" box="[227,341,467,493]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF13929EBD2C6E0FEAA5ADB" bold="true" box="[227,341,467,493]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF13929EBD2C533FA925996" blockId="95.[227,1437,512,672]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
Because of their general shape, their prominent posterodorsal angle and their salient postero-ventral angle, these otoliths seems to match very well with those of the sparid genus 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF13929EF5EC512FB2A590D" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1830" box="[1135,1237,545,571]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sparidae" genus="Pagellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF13929EF5EC512FB2A590D" box="[1135,1237,545,571]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Pagellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFF13929EE23C512FA67590D" author="Nolf D." box="[1298,1432,545,571]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" refId="ref55873" refString="Nolf D. 2018. Otoliths of Fishes from the North Sea and the English Channel. Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences, Brussels." type="book" year="2018">Nolf (2018</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 56), where an ontogenetic series of the Recent 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF13929E815C570FB215968" authority="(Brunnich, 1768)" baseAuthorityName="Brunnich" baseAuthorityYear="1768" box="[804,1246,579,606]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sparidae" genus="Pagellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogaraveo">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF13929E815C570FBF2596B" box="[804,1037,579,605]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Pagellus bogaraveo</emphasis>
(Brünnich, 1768)
</taxonomicName>
is figured. Also, the ontogenetic series of the Recent taxon, with a more anteriorly located pronounced rounding in the ventral rim of small specimens, matches very well with the ontogenetic changes seen in the fossils.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
